      <section eId="sec_581_401">
        <num>581-401</num>
        <heading>Surrogacy agreement authorized</heading>
        <subsection eId="sec_581_401__subsec_a">
          <num>(a)</num>
          <content>
            <p>If eligible under this\narticle to enter into a surrogacy agreement, a person acting as\nsurrogate, the spouse of the person acting as surrogate, if applicable,\nand the intended parent or parents may enter into a surrogacy agreement\nwhich will be enforceable provided the surrogacy agreement meets the\nrequirements of this article.\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_581_401__subsec_b">
          <num>(b)</num>
          <content>
            <p>A surrogacy agreement shall not apply to the birth of a child\nconceived by means of sexual intercourse, or where the person acting as\nsurrogate contributed the egg used in conception.\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
        <subsection eId="sec_581_401__subsec_c">
          <num>(c)</num>
          <content>
            <p>A surrogacy agreement may provide for payment of compensation\nunder part five of this article.\n</p>
          </content>
        </subsection>
      </section>
